description:
Oracle has filed a motion to dismiss a fraud claim in a trademark dispute over its long-standing “JAVASCRIPT” mark. The motion – submitted to the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) Trademark Trial and Appeal Board (TTAB) – argues that the petitioner, Deno Land Inc., has failed to state a plausible claim for fraud.... Read more »

The post Oracle seeks dismissal of fraud claim in JavaScript trademark case appeared first on Developer Tech News.
title: Oracle seeks dismissal of fraud claim in JavaScript trademark case
